    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-27T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-27T07:00:00-05:00" n="575"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 800.852/90</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-27T21:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 27, 1918, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 28, 5.47 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No. 13. Supplementing my serial No. 3<note n="1" xml:id="d575fn1">Not printed;
                        gives sailing dates and destinations of 23 chartered ships totaling 151,266
                        tons.</note>. All charters formally executed. Certified copies being sent by
                    pouch. <hi rend="italic">Shakano-o</hi> leaves May 20 for Seattle; <hi
                        rend="italic">Kunajiri</hi> leaves in May for Tacoma; all others as
                    previously reported in my No. 3. No chartered ships will be delivered at
                    Japanese ports.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MRS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
